# CustomArc API — Agent Guide

> Read before any change under `apps/api/` or `packages/db/`. Spec: `docs/phase-1/spec.md`.

## Stack

Bun · Elysia · Prisma (`@customarc/db`) · Zod (`@customarc/shared`) · better-auth

## Package Manager

`pnpm` · run API: `pnpm api` · typecheck: `pnpm --filter @customarc/api typecheck`

## Architecture (mandatory)

```
routes → service → repo → prisma
```

- Routes: HTTP only (parse, call service, map `ok`/`err`). No Prisma.
- Services: business rules. Framework-agnostic. No request/response objects.
- Repos: persistence only. No business rules.
- Errors: throw `ApiError` helpers from `src/errors.ts`. App maps them once in `app.ts`.

## Auth (settled)

- **Passwordless only:** magic link **and** email OTP + optional Google OAuth.
- **No passwords.** Do not enable `emailAndPassword`. Do not add password routes/UI.
- Library: better-auth (`src/modules/auth/`). No hand-rolled sessions/JWT.
- Guard: `.use(withAuth)` → `user` / `session` on context.
- Never trust `x-user-id` or client-sent user ids.
- New users → `creditsService.grantFreeAllocation` via better-auth `databaseHooks`.
- Endpoints: magic link `POST /api/auth/sign-in/magic-link`; OTP send `POST /api/auth/email-otp/send-verification-otp` + sign-in `POST /api/auth/sign-in/email-otp`.

## Practices

- **DRY** — shared helpers once; no copy-paste `requireUser`.
- **KISS / YAGNI** — shortest correct path; no speculative abstractions.
- **Decouple** — modules import services, not each other's repos/Prisma.
- **Fail fast** — required env as named consts in `src/env.ts` (`RESEND_API_KEY`, `AUTH_SECRET`, …); validate bodies with Elysia `t` / shared Zod.
- **Idempotent writes** where money/credits matter (`correlationId`).
- Short files, clear names, no drive-by refactors outside the task.

## Module layout

```
src/modules/<name>/
  routes.ts   # Elysia adapter
  service.ts  # domain
  repo.ts     # optional Prisma
```

Auth special files: `instance.ts` (better-auth), `plugin.ts` (`authPlugin` mount + `withAuth` guard), `mail.ts` (magic-link + OTP delivery).

Protected routes: `.use(withAuth)` then read `user` / `session` from context.

## Schema

- Source of truth: `packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Auth tables already map better-auth core (`users` / `sessions` / `accounts` / `verifications`).
- Migrations via Prisma only — never edit production DB by hand.

## Anti-patterns

- Business logic in routes
- Hand-rolled auth / password login
- Skipping the service layer for “just one query”
- Swallowing errors or returning inconsistent envelopes
- Secrets in code (use `.env`; update `.env.example`)
